{{Infobox Painting | image_file=Rubens - La Chasse au tigre.jpg | image_size=270px | title=The Tiger Hunt | artist=[[Peter Paul Rubens]] | year=1615—1616 | medium=[[Oil painting|Oil]] on [[canvas]] | height_metric=256 | width_metric=324 | museum =[[Musée des Beaux-Arts de Rennes]] | city = [[Rennes]] }} '''''The Tiger Hunt''''' is a large painting by [[Peter Paul Rubens]], featuring a hunt for a tiger. It dates to between 1615 and 1616 and is one of the four hunting paintings, commissioned by [[Maximilian I, Elector of Bavaria]] to decorate the [[Schleissheim Palace#Old Schleissheim Palace|old Schleissheim Palace]]. The cycle was seized during the [[Napoleonic Wars]] and this painting is now in [[Musée des Beaux-Arts de Rennes]].<ref>http://www.mbar.org/collections/guide/14-18/essai_menu.php</ref>
